<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<NamedCredential xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <label>AI Provider</label>
    <endpoint>https://api.example.com</endpoint>
    <principalType>NamedUser</principalType>
    <protocol>Password</protocol>
    <username>your-api-key-here</username>
    <password>your-api-secret-here</password>
    <!--
    CONFIGURATION INSTRUCTIONS:
    ============================

    1. Update the endpoint URL based on your AI provider:
       - Anthropic Claude: https://api.anthropic.com
       - OpenAI: https://api.openai.com
       - Azure OpenAI: https://YOUR_RESOURCE_NAME.openai.azure.com
       - Other providers: Consult their API documentation

    2. Configure authentication:
       For API Key authentication (most common):
       - Set principalType to "Anonymous"
       - Remove username/password fields
       - Add custom headers in callout code or use External Credentials

       For Named Credentials with External Credentials:
       - Create an External Credential first
       - Set principalType to "PerUser" or "NamedUser"
       - Link the External Credential

    3. Update AIService.cls:
       - Modify buildRequestPayload() to match your provider's API format
       - Update parseResponse() to handle your provider's response structure
       - Add the correct endpoint path in callAI() method

    4. Grant Salesforce IP Addresses access:
       - Add Salesforce IPs to your AI provider's allowlist if required

    5. Test the integration:
       - Set AIService.setMode(AIService.AIMode.REAL) in anonymous Apex
       - Call DeliveryCopilotService.reviewSolutionDesign('test')
       - Monitor debug logs for any errors

    SECURITY NOTES:
    ===============
    - Never commit actual API keys to version control
    - Use environment-specific configurations
    - Regularly rotate API credentials
    - Monitor API usage and costs
    - Implement rate limiting if needed

    Example configurations are provided in AIService.cls comments.
    -->
</NamedCredential>
